comment: Hill (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact that does not affect Redick's (LAC) RSBQ.
Mahinmi (IND) establishes a legal guarding position prior to the start of the upward shooting motion, and jumps vertically as he contests Redick's (LAC) driving shot attempt.
Allen (IND) makes contact by Jordan's (LAC) waist, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Hill (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Redick (LAC) that does not affect his FOM away from the ball.
George (IND) makes incidental contact with Paul (LAC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Ellis (IND) makes contact with Crawford's (LAC) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Crawford (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that George (IND) was behind the three point line was confirmed.
Allen (IND) and Jordan (LAC) make incidental contact with one another away from the ball.
LATR shows that Crawford's (LAC) right foot is OOB when he gains possession.
Crawford (LAC) controls the ball and throws it into the backcourt. A violation is correctly called, however the clock should have been reset to 00:02.7.
Mbah a Moute (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends George (IND) during the inbounds play.
Due to a clock malfunction that caused the clock to run to 00:00.0, the crew communicated with the Replay Center and determined that 00:00.3 should be placed back on the clock.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Rivers' (LAC) shot occurred after the clock had expired was confirmed.
